                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="131" value="&amp;nbsp;t = 0" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#FF0000;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="88.5" y="1010" width="40" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="132" value="&amp;nbsp;t = 1" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#FF0000;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="100" y="1020" width="80" height="10" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="133" value="&amp;nbsp;t = 2" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#FF0000;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="174" y="1010" width="40" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="134" value="&amp;nbsp;t = 3" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#FF0000;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="204" y="1010" width="39" height="29.25" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="135" value="A" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="33" y="856" width="60" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="136" value="B" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="15" y="895" width="60" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="137" value="Scenario 1:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;A leading B&lt;/span&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontStyle=1;fontSize=16;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="310" y="120" width="190" height="50" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="138" value="Scenario 2:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;B leading A&lt;/span&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=center;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontStyle=1;fontSize=16;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="310" y="610" width="190" height="50" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="139" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;At t=0, A goes from low to high. At this instance, B is still low. In otherwords, since A goes high BEFORE B, the car is moving forward. Between t=0 and t=1, the low to high of A calls the _callback_a function. Since, A != B, count += 1. From t=1 to t=3, B goes from low to high. This calls _callback_b function. Since A==B, count += 1.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;A and B going up, adds 2 to the count. This is in forward motion.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=left;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="122" y="173" width="566" height="100" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="146" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;At t=0, B goes from low to high. At this instance, A is still low. In otherwords, since B goes high BEFORE A, the car is moving forward. Between t=0 and t=1, the low to high of B calls the _callback_b function. Since, B!=A, count -= 1. From t=1 to t=3, A goes from low to high. This calls _callback_a function. Since A==B, count -= 1.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;A and B going up, subtracts 2 from the count. This is in backward motion.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;align=left;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="131" y="660" width="566" height="100" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="147" value="Therefore, backward motion subtracts from count, whereas forward motion adds to count. Count will be used for distance calculation. Let&#39;s say tank moves forward and backward, we measure the DISPLACEMENT. To use the right words, we are measuring the DISPLACEMENT not distance." style="text;strokeColor=none;align=left;fillColor=none;html=1;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="98" y="1060" width="630" height="70" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
            </root>
        </mxGraphModel>
    </diagram>
</mxfile>